Tips for Working with Opportunity Reports

You can use the following columns to provide more detail:
Age—Age counts the number of days passed between opportunity open date and close date.
Stage Duration—The number of days the opportunity was in the stage listed in the Stage column.
Last Activity—The most recent due date of an activity on the opportunity record.

Not all Opportunity Product fields are available in report filters. Create a custom formula field to store its contents and use that formula field in your filter.
You can include the Primary Campaign Source field on all standard opportunity reports.

Use the View filter to limit your opportunity report results. View options vary depending on your organization's Edition and setup.
